TIL the suffix, -stan, used in many Indo-Iranian regions, is Persian for "place of" or "country". Such as Kyrgyzstan, Afghanistan, Kazakhstan, Pakistan, etc...
I'm pretty sure the translation is something closer to 'land of' land of the Afghans, land of Kazakhs etc.
